1 from a motorcycle accident. If personal protection insurance
2 benefits or personal injury benefits described in section 3103(2)
3 are payable to or for the benefit of an injured person under his or
4 her own policy and would also be payable under the policy of his or
5 her spouse, relative, or relative's spouse, the injured person's
6 insurer shall pay all of the benefits up to the coverage level
7 applicable under section 3107c to the injured person's policy, and
8 is not entitled to recoupment from the other insurer.
9 (2) A person who suffers accidental bodily injury while an
10 operator or a passenger of a motor vehicle operated in the business
11 of transporting passengers shall receive the personal protection
12 insurance benefits to which the person is entitled from the insurer
13 of the motor vehicle. This subsection does not apply to a passenger
14 in any of the following, unless the passenger is not entitled to
15 personal protection insurance benefits under any other policy:
16 (a) A school bus, as defined by the department of education,
17 providing transportation not prohibited by law.
18 (b) A bus operated by a common carrier of passengers certified
19 by the department of transportation.
20 (c) A bus operating under a government sponsored
21 transportation program.
22 (d) A bus operated by or providing service to a nonprofit
23 organization.
24 (e) A taxicab insured as prescribed in section 3101 or 3102.
25 (f) A bus operated by a canoe or other watercraft, bicycle, or
26 horse livery used only to transport passengers to or from a
27 destination point.
28 (g) A transportation network company vehicle.
29 (h) A motor vehicle insured under a policy for which the
